## ŌÜĀ’ĖÅ Common Pitfalls & Fixes

### 1. Async/Await Issues
**Problem:** Calling async functions without `await` causes data to not be loaded before rendering.
```javascript
// ŌØī WRONG
renderAvailabilityExecView();
const html = container.innerHTML; // Empty!

// Ō£ģ CORRECT
await renderAvailabilityExecView();
const html = container.innerHTML; // Has content
```

### 2. Falsy Value Defaults
**Problem:** Using `|| defaultValue` with numbers where 0 is valid.
```javascript
// ŌØī WRONG - 0 becomes 1
serviceTier: parseInt(value) || 1

// Ō£ģ CORRECT - 0 stays 0
const tier = parseInt(value);
serviceTier: isNaN(tier) ? 1 : tier
```

### 3. CSV Encoding Issues
CSV files from Excel may be UTF-16LE encoded. Convert to UTF-8:
```bash
iconv -f UTF-16LE -t UTF-8 input.csv > output.csv
```

### 4. Tab-Separated Files
`Autoscaling.csv` uses TABS not commas:
```javascript
const values = line.split('\t');  // NOT split(',')
```

### 5. React Tab Detection
Tabs with `data-react-tab="true"` attribute are handled by React:
```javascript
const isReactTab = navItem.hasAttribute('data-react-tab');
```
To convert to vanilla JS: remove the attribute and add a tab-pane div.

### 6. Filter Visibility
Filters are hidden for certain tabs:
- `executive-overview` (Onboarding Exec View) - filters hidden
- `migration-pipeline` (Onboarding Exec View) - filters hidden
- All other tabs show filters

### 7. View Mode Switching
When switching between Exec/Developer view:
- If current tab has corresponding view, switch to that tab
- Otherwise, default to first visible tab in that section
- Example: On "Autoscaling" in Exec View ŌåÆ switch to "Autoscaling" in Developer View

### 8. Data Aggregation for Karpenter
When a cluster appears multiple times in the same month (different FI/FD combinations):
- **Month Column**: Shows unique months only (no duplicates)
- **Avg CPU**: Aggregated mean across all FI/FD combinations for that cluster+month
- **Improvement**: Compares aggregated latest month vs aggregated previous month
- **Efficiency Indicator**: Calculated from aggregated CPU % and most common environment

### 9. SVG Chart X-Axis Alignment
**Problem:** X-axis labels positioned with CSS percentages don't align with SVG data points.
```javascript
// ŌØī WRONG - CSS percentage positioning doesn't match SVG coordinates
<div class="chart-x-axis">
    ${data.map((d, i) => {
        const xPercent = (i / (data.length - 1)) * 100;
        return `<span style="left: ${xPercent}%">${d.month}</span>`;
    }).join('')}
</div>

// Ō£ģ CORRECT - X-axis labels inside SVG using same coordinates as data points
const xAxisLabels = points.map(p => 
    `<text x="${p.x}" y="${height - 15}" text-anchor="middle">${p.month}</text>`
).join('');
// Include xAxisLabels inside <svg>...</svg>
```

### 10. Page Overflow on Developer View
**Problem:** Wide tables push the page beyond viewport width, hiding header/buttons.
**Solution:** Apply these constraints:
```css
/* Prevent page from extending beyond viewport */
html, body {
    overflow-x: hidden !important;
    max-width: 100vw !important;
}

.main-content {
    overflow-x: hidden !important;
    max-width: calc(100vw - 280px) !important; /* Accounts for sidebar */
}

.page-header, .content-layout, .content-area, .tab-pane {
    max-width: 100% !important;
    overflow-x: hidden !important;
}

/* Tables scroll inside their container */
.table-container {
    overflow-x: auto !important;
    max-width: 100% !important;
}
```

