## ­¤ōØ Adding New Features

### Adding a New Vanilla JS Tab

1. **Add navigation item** in `index.html`:
```html
<div class="nav-subitem" data-tab="my-new-tab" data-view="exec">
    <span class="nav-text">My Tab</span>
</div>
```

2. **Add tab pane** in `index.html`:
```html
<div class="tab-pane" id="my-new-tab">
    <div class="tab-header">
        <h2>My Tab</h2>
    </div>
    <div id="my-tab-content"></div>
</div>
```

3. **Add render function** in `fkp-dashboard.js`:
```javascript
function renderMyTab() {
    const container = document.getElementById('my-tab-content');
    // Render content
}
```

4. **Add to refreshCurrentTab()**:
```javascript
case 'my-new-tab':
    renderMyTab();
    break;
```

5. **Add to tabTitles** for header:
```javascript
'my-new-tab': {
    title: 'Section Name',
    subtitle: 'Tab Name'
}
```

### Adding New Data

1. Place CSV in `assets/data/`
2. Create async load function with caching
3. Use `Promise.all()` for parallel loading
4. Handle both success and fallback cases

